28/11/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski met with the administration board of the Association of Local Government Units (ZELS) on Monday (November 27th). 
Gruevski reportedly promised ZELS that the cabinet would service 90% of schools' debt and provide 8.5m euros for computerisation of primary and secondary schools throughout Macedonia. 
In addition, the cabinet will help fund construction of 85 sports facilities and will provide buses for schools in rural areas. 
ZELS representatives, meanwhile, urged the cabinet to help cover huge municipal debts. 
(Vecer - 28/11/06; MIA, A1 TV - 27/11/06)
